Package: DGQGSI
Type: Package
Title: Desired-Gain Selection Index and Quadratic Genomic Selection Index
    Tools for Plant Breeding
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(
      given   = "Félicien",
      family  = "Akohoue",
      email   = "akohoue.f@gmail.com",
      role    = c("aut", "cre"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2160-0182")
    )
Description: Provides tools for multi-trait selection in plant breeding
    programs using desired-gain-based selection indices. Implements two
    complementary workflows: a desired-gain selection index optimization
    (DGSI) that estimates index weights whose realized genetic gains match
    breeder-defined targets, following Joukhadar et al. (2024)
    <doi:10.3389/fpls.2024.1337388>; and a desired-gain quadratic genomic
    selection index (QGSI) that incorporates linear and quadratic genomic
    estimated breeding value (GEBV) components to capture nonlinear trait
    interactions, following Ceron-Rojas et al. (2026)
    <doi:10.1038/s41467-026-69890-3>. Additional tools include automatic
    construction of the quadratic desired-gain matrix, a high-level pipeline
    wrapper for running one or both workflows, and a comparison helper that
    merges and ranks genotype-level outputs from both methods.
